%% Diagram: How a missing width/height (or aspect-ratio) creates CLS.
%% Compares the two timelines: with a presentational hint the box is
%% reserved at first layout; without it the box collapses to zero
%% and content reflows when image bytes arrive.
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant Layout as "Layout engine"
    participant Net as "Network"
    participant Paint as "Compositor"

    Note over Layout,Paint: With width / height (or aspect-ratio)
    Layout->>Layout: Parse <img width=800 height=600>
    Layout->>Layout: Reserve box (auto 800/600)
    Layout->>Paint: First paint with placeholder box
    Net-->>Layout: Image bytes arrive
    Layout->>Paint: Paint pixels into reserved box
    Note right of Paint: CLS contribution: 0

    Note over Layout,Paint: Without width / height
    Layout->>Layout: Parse <img>
    Layout->>Layout: Box collapses to 0 x 0
    Layout->>Paint: First paint, no space reserved
    Net-->>Layout: Image bytes arrive
    Layout->>Layout: Reflow (push content down)
    Layout->>Paint: Re-paint with shifted layout
    Note right of Paint: CLS contribution: > 0
